1. Introduction

TicketSense is a web-based Helpdesk Ticket Classifier and Router designed to automate customer support ticket management. The application classifies incoming support tickets into predefined categories and routes them to the appropriate department using machine learning and Flask-based web technologies. The goal is to reduce manual effort, improve response time, and increase the efficiency of customer support operations.

Part 1 – Domain Research
1. Domain Introduction
What is the Helpdesk Ticket Management Domain?

A helpdesk ticket management system is software that allows organizations to receive, track, categorize, assign, and resolve customer support requests. Each customer issue is represented as a ticket that moves through various stages until resolution.

Examples of organizations using helpdesk systems include:

IT companies
Software firms
Banks
Hospitals
Educational institutions
E-commerce companies
Government organizations
Why is this Domain Important?

Customer satisfaction depends heavily on quick issue resolution. As organizations grow, manually handling thousands of support requests becomes impractical. Helpdesk systems provide:

Centralized issue management
Faster response times
Better resource allocation
Improved communication
Performance monitoring
Historical record keeping
