Flask Architecture

Flask follows the Model–View–Controller (MVC) pattern (or a lightweight variation of it):

Model: Database layer
View: HTML templates (Jinja2)
Controller: Flask routes and business logic
Benefits
Modular
Lightweight
Easy to extend
Suitable for rapid development
Request–Response Cycle
User sends an HTTP request.
Flask receives the request.
The appropriate route is matched.
Business logic executes.
Database is accessed if needed.
A response is generated.
HTML is rendered using Jinja2.
The browser displays the page.
